I was thinking about this for a while, but I think this isn't the right fix for this.
The stacktrace in #7034 makes it clear that this NullPointerException occurs when shutting down a game, so adjusting the preffered size just before the game is closed doesn't really make sense to me.
That's why I'd recommend making this method no-op if chat is null i.e.
if (chat == null) {
  return;
}
